[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":328},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fadobexd\u002F2019\u002F07\u002F23\u002Fhow-to-open-adobe-xd-design-files\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fadobexd\u002F2019\u002F07\u002F23\u002Fhow-to-open-adobe-xd-design-files\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fadobexd\u002F2019\u002F07\u002F23\u002Fhow-to-open-adobe-xd-design-files\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fadobexd\u002F2019\u002F07\u002F23\u002Fhow-to-open-adobe-xd-design-files\u002F":318,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fadobexd\u002F2019\u002F07\u002F23\u002Fhow-to-open-adobe-xd-design-files\u002F":327},"\u002Fadobexd\u002F20190723\u002F1858934129\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":302,"date":303,"description":304,"extension":305,"lang":306,"meta":307,"navigation":308,"path":309,"readingMinutes":310,"seo":311,"standalone":312,"stem":313,"tags":314,"tldr":315,"updated":303,"url":316,"__hash__":317},"content\u002Fen\u002FAdobeXD\u002Fhow-to-open-adobe-xd-design-files.md","How to Open Adobe XD Design Files (Plus Online Specs)","1540106130",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":290},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,27,37,44,47,53,64,70,73,79,87,93,96,102,106,109,115,119,127,132,139,144,149,154,157,163,166,172,175,181,185,201,206,209,215,219,222,228,231,237,240,246,250,265,274,280,284],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"Frontend devs usually receive an Adobe XD online spec to work from. But if the designer is on the free plan, things get a bit different — you might just get the raw XD file. So how do you open it and turn it into an online spec?",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"the-raw-xd-file","The raw XD file",[17,25,26],{},"Designers usually use a personal Adobe XD account, which comes in two plans:",[28,29,30,34],"ul",{},[31,32,33],"li",{},"Starter (free)",[31,35,36],{},"Monthly subscription",[17,38,39],{},[40,41],"img",{"alt":42,"src":43},"Adobe XD plans","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FPG2Uq4q.png",[17,45,46],{},"On the free plan, you only get one shared online spec link at a time.",[17,48,49],{},[40,50],{"alt":51,"src":52},"One share link","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002F1SZvlec.png",[17,54,55,56,63],{},"For an example, I'll use ",[57,58,62],"a",{"href":59,"rel":60},"https:\u002F\u002Fchallenge.thef2e.com\u002Fworks\u002Fuiux",[61],"nofollow","The F2E — Frontend Hyperbolic Time Chamber"," and download one of the raw XD design files there.",[17,65,66],{},[40,67],{"alt":68,"src":69},"Raw XD design file","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FEKsQcVU.png",[17,71,72],{},"Most raw XD files live on Google Drive. Some designers also provide PNG \u002F JPG \u002F SVG \u002F PDF directly.",[17,74,75],{},[40,76],{"alt":77,"src":78},"Google Drive","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FQlb8nOC.png",[17,80,81,82,86],{},"After downloading, if you try to open the file and see ",[83,84,85],"code",{},"This was created with a newer version of Adobe XD. Please update Adobe XD to open it",", your Adobe XD is too old.",[17,88,89],{},[40,90],{"alt":91,"src":92},"Update Adobe XD","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FaEd82YW.png",[17,94,95],{},"After updating, you can open the file.",[17,97,98],{},[40,99],{"alt":100,"src":101},"Opened design","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FNO5JB1K.png",[12,103,105],{"id":104},"checking-xd-spacing","Checking XD spacing",[17,107,108],{},"How do you check spec details on the design? Click an element, then hold ALT to see distance measurements to other elements.",[17,110,111],{},[40,112],{"alt":113,"src":114},"Spacing measurements","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FbO9HlfK.png",[12,116,118],{"id":117},"online-specs","Online specs",[17,120,121,122,126],{},"The hold-ALT approach is clunky, and you might accidentally edit the original. A better way is to convert the design to an online spec. As a frontend dev you really want the proper spec view. Click the ",[123,124,125],"strong",{},"Share"," button at the top.",[17,128,129],{},[40,130],{"alt":125,"src":131},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FqGbPdod.png",[17,133,134,135,138],{},"Pick ",[123,136,137],{},"Share for Development",".",[17,140,141],{},[40,142],{"alt":137,"src":143},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002F5KOCC3y.png",[17,145,146,138],{},[123,147,148],{},"Create Link",[17,150,151],{},[40,152],{"alt":148,"src":153},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FrYyw0CU.png",[17,155,156],{},"Wait a moment while it generates.",[17,158,159],{},[40,160],{"alt":161,"src":162},"Generating...","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FJStk3VS.png",[17,164,165],{},"Once done you get the file link.",[17,167,168],{},[40,169],{"alt":170,"src":171},"File link","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FM4OtFCQ.png",[17,173,174],{},"Open the link in your browser and you'll see the online spec view.",[17,176,177],{},[40,178],{"alt":179,"src":180},"Online spec","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FCyGMsoq.png",[12,182,184],{"id":183},"cant-create-more-online-links","Can't create more online links",[17,186,187,188,191,192,195,196,138],{},"If you see ",[83,189,190],{},"Upgrade to create unlimited links to share with developers",", click ",[83,193,194],{},"Manage Links"," at the bottom or go to ",[57,197,200],{"href":198,"rel":199},"https:\u002F\u002Fassets.adobe.com\u002Flinks",[61],"Adobe's link manager",[17,202,203],{},[40,204],{"alt":194,"src":205},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FrzM6ODi.png",[17,207,208],{},"Delete shared files in the Adobe XD link manager.",[17,210,211],{},[40,212],{"alt":213,"src":214},"Delete files","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FrAuZufX.png",[12,216,218],{"id":217},"switching-adobe-xd-to-simplified-chinese","Switching Adobe XD to Simplified Chinese",[17,220,221],{},"Bonus — how to switch Adobe XD to Simplified Chinese (no Traditional Chinese option, sadly). Click the top-left Menu.",[17,223,224],{},[40,225],{"alt":226,"src":227},"Menu","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002Fev6W50W.png",[17,229,230],{},"Help → Language.",[17,232,233],{},[40,234],{"alt":235,"src":236},"Help → Language","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FkThPLWU.png",[17,238,239],{},"Pick Simplified Chinese.",[17,241,242],{},[40,243],{"alt":244,"src":245},"Restart XD afterwards","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FXrMPSw2.png",[12,247,249],{"id":248},"wrapping-up","Wrapping up",[17,251,252,253,258,259,264],{},"If you want to learn more about Adobe XD, you can consider Hexschool's ",[57,254,257],{"href":255,"rel":256},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.udemy.com\u002Fadobe-xd-hexschool\u002F",[61],"Adobe XD course (Mandarin)"," (cheaper to ",[57,260,263],{"href":261,"rel":262},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.hexschool.com\u002Fcourses\u002F",[61],"buy from their official site",").",[17,266,267,268,273],{},"If you need designs to practise UI work, check out ",[57,269,272],{"href":270,"rel":271},"https:\u002F\u002Fchallenge.thef2e.com",[61],"The F2E — Frontend Hyperbolic Time Chamber (Mandarin)",". 200+ designs accumulated, more than enough to practise one per day (currently only up to round 2, of 9 total rounds).",[17,275,276],{},[40,277],{"alt":278,"src":279},"Lots of UI designs","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FkaQvKOh.png",[12,281,283],{"id":282},"source","Source",[17,285,286],{},[57,287,289],{"href":59,"rel":288},[61],"The F2E — Frontend Hyperbolic Time Chamber — UI track (Mandarin)",{"title":291,"searchDepth":292,"depth":292,"links":293},"",2,[294,295,296,297,298,299,300,301],{"id":14,"depth":292,"text":15},{"id":22,"depth":292,"text":23},{"id":104,"depth":292,"text":105},{"id":117,"depth":292,"text":118},{"id":183,"depth":292,"text":184},{"id":217,"depth":292,"text":218},{"id":248,"depth":292,"text":249},{"id":282,"depth":292,"text":283},"AdobeXD","2019-07-23 09:31:27","Frontend devs usually receive an Adobe XD online spec to work from. But if the designer is on the free plan, you might get the raw XD file instead. Here's how to open it and how to share the design as an online spec yourself.","md","en",{},true,"\u002Fen\u002Fadobexd\u002Fhow-to-open-adobe-xd-design-files","2",{"title":6,"description":304},false,"en\u002FAdobeXD\u002Fhow-to-open-adobe-xd-design-files",[302],null,"\u002Fen\u002Fadobexd\u002F2019\u002F07\u002F23\u002Fhow-to-open-adobe-xd-design-files\u002F","YVzG1PJsZo6Q7r4ZEv34nI-WMdL-DEYhhZDPKDcxCVs",{"newer":319,"older":323},{"url":320,"title":321,"date":322},"\u002Fen\u002Flearning\u002F2019\u002F07\u002F23\u002Fmy-blogging-philosophy\u002F","My Blogging Philosophy","2019-07-23 21:14:06",{"url":324,"title":325,"date":326},"\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2019\u002F07\u002F22\u002Fkoa-saga-heroku-deploy\u002F","Koa Saga: Deploying to Heroku","2019-07-22 21:39:03",[],1784020342890]